CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 26, 1958, pg. 4 reads: "Labor Supports Its Friends Teamsters local 609 Cope...Endorses ENTIRE Lawrence-Leader Ticket...Left to right, seated: James F. Clarke, Mrs. Thelma Lovette and Theodore (Ted) Brown, who are running for committee woman and committee man, respectively, in Fifth District, Fifth Ward; K.Leroy Irvis and William Finch. Standing , same order: Leroy Wilcox and William E. (Bill) Miller, State Workmen's Compensation Referee...K. Leroy Irvis and James F. Clarke regular endorsed democratic candidates for legislature first legislative district - vote for two - primary - May 20th...vote the straight democratic ticket"
TitMainTitle: Group, seated from left: James F. Clarke, Thelma Lovette, Theodore "Ted" Brown, K. Leroy Irvis, and William Finch; standing: Leroy Wilcox and William E. "Bill" Miller, gathered in interior with leaf patterned curtains and mirror during primary election campaign, another version
